    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>131</citedRange> (no image)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>098400</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            <p>Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#chevrollier2018-2019"/>, p. <citedRange>80</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/> <citedRange>68.1742</citedRange></bibl>;
                <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/>, p. <citedRange>101</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested"><name><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></name> 
                        <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#_ας" type="patronymic"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><seg part="F">α</seg></name></persName></persName> 
                    <persName type="divine" ref="#Athanaia"><name nymRef="#Ἀθαναία">Ἀθαναί<unclear>α</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ι</supplied></name></persName> 
                    <gap reason="lost" quantity="4" unit="character"/> 
                    <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">καὶ</supplied> τὰ <w lemma="διάφραγμα">διαφράγ<supplied reason="lost">ματα</supplied></w>                    
                    <lb n="3"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <rs type="office" key="eponymous priest"><w lemma="ἱαριτεύω"><supplied reason="lost">ἱαριτε</supplied><unclear>ύ</unclear>ων</w></rs> <w lemma="ἀνατίθημι">ἀνέ<supplied reason="lost">θηκε</supplied></w>
                    <lb n="3a"/><space quantity="1" unit="line"/>
                </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="1">
                        <lem>Ἀθαναί<unclear>α</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ι</supplied> <gap reason="lost" quantity="4" unit="character"/></lem>
                        <rdg resp="#SECir">Ἀθαναία<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></rdg>
                </app>
                <app loc="2">
                    <lem><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">καὶ</supplied> τὰ</lem>
                    <rdg resp="#SECir"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>τα</rdg>
                </app>
                </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><supplied reason="lost">Untel</supplied> fils de <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>as a consacré à Athèna <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="lost">et</supplied> 
                la barrière <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> au cours de sa prêtrise.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><supplied reason="lost">So-and-so</supplied> son of <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>as dedicated to Athena <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="lost">and</supplied> 
                the barrier <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> while being priest.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><supplied reason="lost">Il tale</supplied> figlio di <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>as ha dedicato ad Atena <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="lost">e</supplied> 
                lo steccato <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> quando era sacerdote.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The right end of the lines may be calculated from the missing letters at line 3. Hence the lost part at left would have been much larger, so as to
                allow a name and father's name at line 1 and probably the name of one or several other objects dedicated in the gaps. This dedication to Athena by a priest 
                (i.e. eponymous priest of Apollo) is a clue for the existence of a shrine or temple of Athena inside the sanctuary of Apollo, a fact 
                that may also be guessed from the mention of expenses for her priestess in an account of damiergoi (<ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr011600</ref>).</p>
	    <p>On behalf of the probable dimensions of the panel, <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/></bibl> suggests that it should have been fixed upon a building such as a portico or a fountain.
	      In the gap at left of line 3, he plausibly suspects an adjective mentioning the material (wood or stone) of the barrier, duely preceded by <foreign xml:lang="grc">τὰ</foreign>.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
